# Escape Characters in Markdown Blocks

When including markdown syntax examples inside code blocks, escape special characters to prevent the chat view from breaking.

## Common Characters to Escape

- Backticks inside code blocks: use `\`` 
- Triple backticks: use `\`\`\``
- Dollar signs (LaTeX): use `\$`

## Examples

```markdown
# ❌ BAD - breaks rendering
Use triple backticks ``` to create code blocks.

# ✅ GOOD - properly escaped
Use triple backticks \`\`\` to create code blocks.
```

When documenting code block syntax:

```markdown
# ❌ BAD
```python
print("hello")
```

# ✅ GOOD
\`\`\`python
print("hello")
\`\`\`
```
